## Raspberry Syrup

1 cup (125g) fresh raspberries
2 cups (400g) superfine sugar
1 cup (230ml) water

1. Add raspberries and sugar into saucepan and muddle together.
2. Add water and bring to a simmer.
3. Stir and simmer for 10 minutes.
4. Strain into container.
5. Add a touch of vodka to help preserve.
6. Store in refrigerator for up to a month.